      <!-- DATA FLOW -->
      <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-pixel); font-size: 12px; color: var(--neon-pink); text-align: center; margin: 40px 0 20px;">
        DATA FLOW
      </h2>

      <div class="bevel-panel mb-4">
        <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-pixel); font-size: 10px; color: var(--neon-green); margin-bottom: 12px;">
          1. POLLING LOOP (Background Task)
        </h3>
        <p style="color: var(--text); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 12px;">
          A single Tokio task runs in the background. Every 3 seconds, it queries the Docker Engine
          through the Unix socket. It fetches containers, services (if Swarm), nodes (if Swarm), and
          system info. The results are serialized into a <code style="color: var(--neon-cyan);">DashboardState</code>
          struct and sent to the Tokio broadcast channel.
        </p>
        <pre class="code-block" data-lang="rust">
<span class="keyword">loop</span> {'{'} 
    <span class="keyword">let</span> state = poll_docker(&amp;client).<span class="keyword">await</span>;
    <span class="keyword">let</span> json = serde_json::to_string(&amp;state)?;
    tx.send(json)?;  <span class="comment">// broadcast to all WS clients</span>
    tokio::time::sleep(Duration::from_secs(3)).<span class="keyword">await</span>;
{'}'}</pre>
      </div>

      <div class="bevel-panel mb-4">
        <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-pixel); font-size: 10px; color: var(--neon-cyan); margin-bottom: 12px;">
          2. WEBSOCKET HANDLER
        </h3>
        <p style="color: var(--text); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 12px;">
          Each WebSocket client subscribes to the same broadcast channel. When the poller sends a new
          state, all clients receive it simultaneously. The handler also validates the auth token on
          upgrade and cleanly handles disconnections.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bevel-panel mb-4">
        <h3 style="font-family: var(--font-pixel); font-size: 10px; color: var(--neon-yellow); margin-bottom: 12px;">
          3. REST API HANDLERS
        </h3>
        <p style="color: var(--text); line-height: 1.8;">
          Actions (start/stop/restart/scale) go through REST endpoints. Each handler validates the
          request, calls the Docker Engine API, and returns the result. All parameters are sanitized
          against a strict regex. Errors are returned as structured JSON вҖ” never raw error strings.
        </p>
      </div>

